Business Brief -- CompuTrac Inc.:
   Company Expects to Post
   Loss for Quarter and Year
For the year-earlier period, the company reported net
income of $298,234, or five cents a share, on revenue of $3
million.
   CompuTrac also said the fourth-quarter charge, in addition
to a charge in the third quarter, will result in a loss for
the fiscal year. A year earlier, the company reported net
income of $145,217, or two cents a share, on revenue of $10.6
million.
   The company took a nonrecurring charge in the third
quarter of $1.8 million, or 20 cents a share, for writing
down the value of its headquarters building.